# Onboarding checklist — {{ .PostName }}

Generated by legion-post-platform. The provisioner created the artifacts in
this directory; the steps below are the manual ones it can't do for you.

## ⚠️ One-time secrets (save these now — not recoverable later)

- **CRM admin login:** `{{ .AdminUsername }}` / `{{ $.AdminPassword }}`
  Hand this to the post's admin over a secure channel, then delete it from
  here. Only the bcrypt hash is stored in `crm/{{ .Client }}.env`.

## 1. Website

- [ ] Move `site/` into a new instance repo (or a subdir of the platform repo).
- [ ] Add the `legion-post-theme` (Hugo Module or submodule).
- [ ] Drop the post's photos into `site/assets/images/`. The homepage hero
      needs two: `hero-bg.jpg` (full-bleed background) and `hero.jpg` (framed
      photo, also the default OG share image). Gallery photos go in their own
      album bundles.
- [ ] Fill the stubbed content pages (history, rental, family programs, etc.)
      — they carry the theme's TODO shortcode markers that show in staging
      and hide in production.
- [ ] Copy the generic shared pages from the Post 5 reference instance —
      they're identical across posts:
      `flag-etiquette.md`, `accessibility.md`,
      `membership/{requirements,why-join,apply}.md`,
      `family/{auxiliary,sons,riders}.md`.
- [ ] `hugo` build locally and review.

## 2. DNS

- [ ] Point `{{ .Domain }}` A record at the VPS (`165.227.26.223`).
- [ ] Point `admin.{{ .Domain }}` A record at the same IP.
- [ ] (If migrating off another host) add 301 redirects from old URLs to
      `caddy/{{ .Domain }}.caddy`.

## 3. Email (forms)

- [ ] Add `{{ .Domain }}` as a sending domain in Resend; add the DKIM/SPF/
      DMARC records to DNS.
- [ ] Create `/srv/secrets/{{ .Domain }}.env` with `RESEND_API_KEY` +
      `EMAIL_FROM`.
- [ ] Wire the contact form into `contact.md` (copy from the reference
      instance) once the sender verifies.

## 4. CRM

- [ ] Deploy `caddy/admin.{{ .Domain }}.caddy` and
      `caddy/{{ .Domain }}.caddy` to `/etc/caddy/sites/`.
- [ ] Deploy `crm/{{ .Client }}.env` to `/srv/secrets/crm-{{ .Client }}.env`
      (mode 600, root-owned).
- [ ] Bring up the CRM container from `crm/docker-compose.snippet.yml`
      (confirm port `{{ .CRMPort }}` is free on the box first).
- [ ] Verify `https://admin.{{ .Domain }}/healthz` returns `ok` and you can
      log in.

## 5. Twilio (SMS reminders — optional, when the post wants it)

- [ ] Create a Twilio subaccount for this post; buy a local number.
- [ ] Fill `TWILIO_ACCOUNT_SID` / `TWILIO_AUTH_TOKEN` / `TWILIO_FROM_NUMBER`
      in `crm/{{ .Client }}.env`; restart the container.
- [ ] Point Twilio's inbound messaging webhook at
      `https://admin.{{ .Domain }}/webhooks/twilio`.
- [ ] Add a test member, confirm the opt-in YES/STOP flow works end-to-end.

